{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":585,"text":"So last year, I ran for mayor\nof my hometown, Tulsa, Oklahoma."},{"time":5009,"text":"And I was the underdog."},{"time":6712,"text":"I was running against\na two-term incumbent,"},{"time":9643,"text":"and my opponent ran\nthe classic partisan playbook."},{"time":13436,"text":"He publicized his endorsement\nof Donald Trump."},{"time":15833,"text":"He publicized a letter\nthat he sent to President Obama"},{"time":18706,"text":"protesting Syrian refugees,"},{"time":20374,"text":"even though none of them\nwere coming to Tulsa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23961,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":25786,"text":"He ran ads on TV that my kids thought\nmade me look like Voldemort,"},{"time":30517,"text":"and sent out little gems\nin the mail, like this."},{"time":36212,"text":"[America's most liberal\nlabor union has endorsed]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":38596,"text":"Never mind that \"America's\nmost liberal labor union,\""},{"time":41746,"text":"as defined by this ad, was actually\nthe Tulsa Firefighters Union,"},{"time":46283,"text":"hardly a famed bastion of liberalism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49005,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":50600,"text":"Never mind that while she was\nrunning for president"},{"time":53775,"text":"and he was serving\nin his final year in that office,"},{"time":56444,"text":"Hillary, Barack and I could just\nnever find the time to get together"},{"time":59889,"text":"and yuck it up about\nthe Tulsa mayor's race."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62278,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":65763,"text":"Never mind that I, like my opponent,"},{"time":69285,"text":"am a Republican."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70651,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":73548,"text":"And so when something like this\nhits you in a campaign,"},{"time":78961,"text":"you have to decide\nhow you're going to respond,"},{"time":82081,"text":"and we had a novel idea."},{"time":84960,"text":"What if, instead of responding\nwith partisanship,"},{"time":89127,"text":"we responded with a focus on results?"},{"time":91937,"text":"What if we ran a campaign"},{"time":94214,"text":"that was not about running\nagainst someone,"},{"time":98231,"text":"but was about bringing people together\nbehind a common vision?"},{"time":101723,"text":"And so we decided\nto respond not with a negative ad"},{"time":106661,"text":"but with something people\nfind even sexier --"},{"time":109979,"text":"data points."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111178,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":113186,"text":"And so we emphasized things like\nincreasing per capita income in our city,"},{"time":118859,"text":"increasing our city's population,"},{"time":121851,"text":"and we stuck to those relentlessly,\nthroughout the campaign,"},{"time":126533,"text":"always bringing it back to those things"},{"time":128939,"text":"by which our voters could measure,\nin a very transparent way,"},{"time":133404,"text":"how we were doing,"},{"time":134597,"text":"and hold me accountable if I got elected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136931,"text":"And a funny thing happened\nwhen we did that."},{"time":139619,"text":"Tulsa is home to one of the most vibrant"},{"time":141550,"text":"young professional\npopulations in the country,"},{"time":143931,"text":"and they took notice of this approach."},{"time":147142,"text":"We have in our culture in our city,"},{"time":149682,"text":"an ethos where our business leaders\ndon't just run companies,"},{"time":153254,"text":"they run philanthropic\ninstitutions and nonprofits,"},{"time":157621,"text":"and those folks took notice."},{"time":159730,"text":"We have parents who are willing\nto sacrifice today"},{"time":163714,"text":"so that their kids\ncan have a better future,"},{"time":165937,"text":"and those people took notice, too."},{"time":168177,"text":"And so on election day,"},{"time":170532,"text":"I, G.T. Bynum,"},{"time":172453,"text":"a guy whose name reminds people\nof a circus promoter ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176034,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":177922,"text":"a guy with the raw animal magnetism\nof a young Orville Redenbacher ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182907,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":185733,"text":"I won the election by 17 points."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189693,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":194375,"text":"And we did it with the support\nof Republicans and Democrats."},{"time":199130,"text":"Now, why is that story\nand that approach so novel?"},{"time":204021,"text":"Why do we always allow ourselves"},{"time":206010,"text":"to fall back on\nphilosophical disagreements"},{"time":209083,"text":"that ultimately lead to division?"},{"time":214014,"text":"I believe it is because politicians"},{"time":216554,"text":"find it easier to throw\nthe red meat out to the base"},{"time":219746,"text":"than to innovate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221228,"text":"The conventional wisdom\nis that to win an election,"},{"time":223903,"text":"you have to dumb it down"},{"time":225349,"text":"and play to your constituencies'\nbasest, divisive instincts."},{"time":231950,"text":"And when somebody\nwins an election like that,"},{"time":234835,"text":"they win, that's true,"},{"time":237676,"text":"but the rest of us lose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240721,"text":"And so what we need to do is think\nabout how can we change that dynamic."},{"time":244977,"text":"How can we move in a direction"},{"time":248540,"text":"where partisanship\nis replaced with policy?"},{"time":251502,"text":"And fortunately, there's a growing\nbipartisan movement across this country"},{"time":255027,"text":"that is doing just that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257557,"text":"One of its heroes\nis a guy named Mitch Daniels."},{"time":260654,"text":"Mitch Daniels served\nas George W. Bush's budget director,"},{"time":264367,"text":"and during that time,"},{"time":265669,"text":"he created what was called the PART tool."},{"time":268529,"text":"The PART tool allowed people to evaluate\na broad range of federal programs"},{"time":274181,"text":"and apply numerical scoring for them"},{"time":277150,"text":"on things like program management\nand project results."},{"time":280563,"text":"And using this, they evaluated\nover a thousand federal programs."},{"time":285946,"text":"Over 150 programs\nhad their funding reduced"},{"time":289439,"text":"because they could not\ndemonstrate success."},{"time":293003,"text":"But unfortunately, there wasn't ever\na well-publicized increase in funding"},{"time":297218,"text":"for those programs\nthat did demonstrate success,"},{"time":300003,"text":"and because of this, the program\nwas never really popular with Congress,"},{"time":303789,"text":"and was eventually shuttered."},{"time":305416,"text":"But the spirit of that program lived on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308091,"text":"Mitch Daniels went home to Indiana,"},{"time":310377,"text":"ran for governor, got elected,"},{"time":312100,"text":"and applied the same premise\nto state programs,"},{"time":315902,"text":"reducing funding for those programs\nthat could not demonstrate success,"},{"time":320506,"text":"but this time, he very publicly\nincreased funding for those programs"},{"time":325840,"text":"that could demonstrate success,"},{"time":327372,"text":"things like increasing\nthe number of state troopers"},{"time":330683,"text":"that they needed to have,"},{"time":331911,"text":"reducing wait times at the DMV --"},{"time":334333,"text":"and today, Mitch Daniels\nis the president of Purdue University,"},{"time":337977,"text":"applying yet again the same principles,"},{"time":340183,"text":"this time at the higher ed level,"},{"time":342008,"text":"and he's done that in order to keep\ntuition levels for students there flat"},{"time":346182,"text":"for half a decade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348752,"text":"Now, while Mitch Daniels\napplied this at the federal level,"},{"time":351864,"text":"the state level, and in higher ed,"},{"time":353681,"text":"the guy that really cracked\nthe code for cities"},{"time":356831,"text":"is a Democrat, Martin O'Malley,"},{"time":359491,"text":"during his time as Mayor of Baltimore."},{"time":362079,"text":"Now, when Mayor O'Malley took office,"},{"time":363914,"text":"he was a big fan of what they'd been\nable to do in New York City"},{"time":367398,"text":"when it came to fighting crime."},{"time":369727,"text":"When Rudy Giuliani first became\nMayor of New York,"},{"time":372775,"text":"crime statistics were collected\non a monthly, even an annual basis,"},{"time":377870,"text":"and then police resources would be\nallocated based on those statistics."},{"time":382174,"text":"Giuliani shrunk that time frame,\nso that crime statistics"},{"time":385857,"text":"would be collected on a daily,\neven hourly basis,"},{"time":389373,"text":"and then police resources\nwould be allocated"},{"time":392698,"text":"to those areas quickly where crimes\nwere occurring today"},{"time":396652,"text":"rather than where\nthey were occurring last quarter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400700,"text":"Well, O'Malley loved that approach,\nand he applied it in Baltimore."},{"time":403939,"text":"And he applied it to the two areas\nthat were most problematic for Baltimore"},{"time":409598,"text":"from a crime-fighting standpoint."},{"time":411241,"text":"We call these the kidneys of death."},{"time":413606,"text":"[Baltimore homicides and shootings, 1999]"},{"time":415599,"text":"So there they are, the kidneys."},{"time":417808,"text":"Now watch this."},{"time":419066,"text":"Watch what happens\nwhen you apply data in real time"},{"time":422348,"text":"and deploy resources quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427401,"text":"In a decade, they reduced\nviolent crime in Baltimore"},{"time":429942,"text":"by almost 50 percent, using this approach,"},{"time":432545,"text":"but the genius of what O'Malley did"},{"time":435109,"text":"was not that he just did\nwhat some other city was doing."},{"time":437999,"text":"Lots of us mayors do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":439737,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":441175,"text":"He realized that the same approach\ncould be used to all of the problems"},{"time":445636,"text":"that his city faced."},{"time":447132,"text":"And so they applied it\nto issue after issue in Baltimore,"},{"time":449824,"text":"and today, it's being used\nby mayors across the country"},{"time":453998,"text":"to deal with some\nof our greatest challenges."},{"time":456157,"text":"And the overall approach\nis a very simple one --"},{"time":459330,"text":"identify the goal\nthat you want to achieve;"},{"time":462176,"text":"identify a measurement\nby which you can track progress"},{"time":465552,"text":"toward that goal;"},{"time":467045,"text":"identify a way of testing that measurement\ncheaply and quickly;"},{"time":473252,"text":"and then deploy whatever strategies\nyou think would work,"},{"time":477689,"text":"test them,"},{"time":479138,"text":"reduce funding for the strategies\nthat don't work,"},{"time":482178,"text":"and put your money\ninto those strategies that do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485474,"text":"Today, Atlanta is using this\nto address housing issues"},{"time":488911,"text":"for their homeless population."},{"time":490689,"text":"Philadelphia has used this\nto reduce their crime rates"},{"time":493626,"text":"to levels not enjoyed since the 1960s."},{"time":496634,"text":"Louisville has used this\nnot just for their city"},{"time":500034,"text":"but in a community-wide effort\nbringing resources together"},{"time":503997,"text":"to address vacant\nand abandoned properties."},{"time":507275,"text":"And I am using this approach in Tulsa."},{"time":509966,"text":"I want Tulsa to be a world-class city,"},{"time":513141,"text":"and we cannot do that\nif we aren't clear in what our goals are"},{"time":517411,"text":"and we don't use evidence\nand evaluation to accomplish them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522937,"text":"Now, what's interesting,\nand we've found in implementing this,"},{"time":526033,"text":"a lot of people, when you talk about data,"},{"time":529598,"text":"people think of that\nas a contrast to creativity."},{"time":533337,"text":"What we've found\nis actually quite the opposite."},{"time":535646,"text":"We've found it to be an engine\nfor creative problem-solving,"},{"time":538710,"text":"because when you're focused on a goal,"},{"time":542044,"text":"and you can test\ndifferent strategies quickly,"},{"time":544878,"text":"the sky's the limit on the different\nthings that you can test out."},{"time":548267,"text":"You can come up with any strategy\nthat you can come up with"},{"time":551362,"text":"and utilize and try and test it"},{"time":553268,"text":"until you find something that works,\nand then you double down on that."},{"time":556578,"text":"The other area that we've found\nthat it lends itself to creativity"},{"time":560735,"text":"is that it breaks down\nthose old silos of ownership"},{"time":563996,"text":"that we run into so often in government."},{"time":566998,"text":"It allows you to draw\nall the stakeholders in your community"},{"time":570682,"text":"that care about homelessness\nor crime-fighting or education"},{"time":575638,"text":"or vacant and abandoned properties,"},{"time":578290,"text":"and bring those people to the table"},{"time":580363,"text":"so you can work together\nto address your common goal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584657,"text":"Now, in Tulsa, we're applying this"},{"time":586339,"text":"to things that are\ncommon city initiatives,"},{"time":590219,"text":"things like, as you've heard\nnow repeatedly,"},{"time":592497,"text":"public safety -- that's an obvious one;"},{"time":595037,"text":"improving our employee\nmorale at the city --"},{"time":597736,"text":"we don't think you could do good things\nunless you've got happy employees;"},{"time":602270,"text":"improving the overall street quality\nthroughout our community."},{"time":606533,"text":"But we're also applying it\nto things that are not so traditional"},{"time":610787,"text":"when you think about\nwhat cities are responsible for,"},{"time":613597,"text":"things like increasing per capita income,"},{"time":616039,"text":"increasing our population,"},{"time":617914,"text":"improving our high school\ngraduation rates,"},{"time":620520,"text":"and perhaps the greatest challenge\nthat we face as a city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626937,"text":"At the dawn of the 1920s,"},{"time":628827,"text":"Tulsa was home to the most vibrant\nAfrican American community in the country."},{"time":632549,"text":"The Greenwood section of our city\nwas known as Black Wall Street."},{"time":637842,"text":"In 1921, in one night,"},{"time":640502,"text":"Tulsa experienced the worst race riot\nin American history."},{"time":644755,"text":"Black Wall Street\nwas burned to the ground,"},{"time":648185,"text":"and today, a child that is born"},{"time":650748,"text":"in the most predominantly\nAfrican American part of our city"},{"time":653622,"text":"is expected to live 11 years less\nthan a kid that's born elsewhere in Tulsa."},{"time":659555,"text":"Now, for us, this is a unifying issue."},{"time":663740,"text":"Four years from now, we will recognize"},{"time":666421,"text":"the 100th commemoration\nof that awful event,"},{"time":670699,"text":"and in Tulsa, we are bringing\nevery tool that we can"},{"time":675045,"text":"to address that life-expectancy disparity,"},{"time":677676,"text":"and we're not checking\nparty registration cards"},{"time":680058,"text":"at the door to the meetings."},{"time":682400,"text":"We don't care who\nyou voted for for president"},{"time":684790,"text":"if you want to help restore\nthe decade of life"},{"time":687488,"text":"that's being stolen\nfrom these kids right now."},{"time":690583,"text":"And so we've got white folks\nand black folks,"},{"time":694011,"text":"Hispanic folks and Native American folks,"},{"time":696330,"text":"we've got members of Congress,\nmembers of the city council,"},{"time":699196,"text":"business leaders, religious leaders,"},{"time":700945,"text":"Trump people and Hillary people,"},{"time":703245,"text":"all joined by one common belief,"},{"time":706214,"text":"and that is that a kid should have\nan equal shot at a good life in our city,"},{"time":710277,"text":"regardless of what part of town\nthey happen to be born in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715129,"text":"Now, how do we go forward with that?"},{"time":718328,"text":"Is that easy to accomplish?"},{"time":720432,"text":"Of course not!"},{"time":722190,"text":"If it were easy to accomplish,"},{"time":724059,"text":"somebody would have already\ndone it before us."},{"time":727013,"text":"But what I love about city government"},{"time":729225,"text":"is that the citizens can create"},{"time":731314,"text":"whatever kind of city\nthey're willing to build,"},{"time":733830,"text":"and in Tulsa, we have decided\nto build a city"},{"time":737291,"text":"where Republicans and Democrats\nuse evidence, data and evaluation"},{"time":742633,"text":"to solve our greatest challenges together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746944,"text":"And if we can do this,"},{"time":748245,"text":"if we can set partisanship aside"},{"time":750919,"text":"in the only state in the whole country\nwhere Barack Obama never carried"},{"time":755416,"text":"a single county,"},{"time":757170,"text":"then you can do it in your town, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759107,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":761234,"text":"Your cities can be saved or squandered"},{"time":764496,"text":"in one generation."},{"time":767036,"text":"So let's agree to set aside\nour philosophical disagreements"},{"time":773084,"text":"and focus on those aspirations\nthat unite us."},{"time":777001,"text":"Let's grasp the opportunity\nthat is presented by innovation"},{"time":781145,"text":"to build better communities\nfor our neighbors."},{"time":784441,"text":"Let's replace a focus on partisan division"},{"time":788378,"text":"with a focus on results."},{"time":791152,"text":"That is the path\nto a better future for us all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795325,"text":"Thank you for your time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796500,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}